<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-05-0405 </DOCNO><TEXT>Arms control purposes include strengthening the framework of deterrenceand reducing the threat of the use of nuclear weapons, reducing the dangersof attack and accidental nuclear war, and allowing more resources forthe civilian economy. The paper briefly describes achievements in armscontrol since World War II. These include the Limited Test Ban Treaty(LTBT), Nonproliferation Treaty (NPT), Anti-Ballistic Missile Treaty(ABMT)-SALT I, SALT II, Threshold Test Ban Treaty (TTBT), Peaceful NuclearExplosions Treaty (PNET), and Nuclear-Free Zones treaties. The authoralso discusses his views on what the priorities of arms control activitiesshould be. (ACR)</TEXT></DOC>